parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag restraint system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the "restraint system failure" message is displayed
the "passenger airbag failure" message is displayed
the "pre-tensioner failure" message is displayed
no airbags deployed in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the "restraint system failure" message is displayed
the "passenger airbag failure" message is displayed
the "pre-tensioner failure" message is displayed
no airbags deployed in an accident
delayed or failed repair of recalled airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy sensor can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the "passenger restraint system malfunction" message is displayed
the seat belt warning beeps even when the passenger seat is empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the N63 engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle overheats
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may produce a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle overheats
the EGR system malfunctions
and there may be a leak of exhaust gas into the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idler pulley bolt can cause the serpentine belt to break, leading to loss of power steering, overheating, and engine damage, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the power steering malfunctions
the battery charging system malfunctions
and the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle overheats
and there may be a coolant leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
